parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel turns independently
the vehicle drifts to the right or left
loss of acceleration when turning
vibration in the driver's mirror
inability to drive in a straight line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering rack and pinion can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Limited turning capability
leaks in the steering rack and pinion
low power steering fluid levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steer-by-wire system can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle is incapable of driving in a straight line
constant drifting to either the right or left
requires frequent steering adjustments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine cuts off while driving
the vehicle jerks before stalling
the vehicle fails to start
system failure warnings appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil filter assembly can cause engine damage and seizure, leading to costly repairs and potentially life-threatening hazards on the road.
symptoms: The engine seizes up
the oil filter assembly's delicate end tip piece breaks or is damaged
the engine is destroyed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop-start system can cause the engine to fail to start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The system failure warning appears on the dashboard
the engine fails to start when the brake pedal is released.
